[49m[38;5;9m- 147     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon Redshift for data aggregation.** Provider profiling requires joining claims, encounters, orders, prescriptions, and outcomes data across millions of records, then aggregating to the provider level. Redshift handles this analytical workload efficiently. The columnar storage is well-suited to the wide, aggregation-heavy queries that provider profiling demands. For quarterly batch workloads, consider Redshift Serverless (pay-per-query) instead of a provisioned cluster. A quarterly aggregation run processing 10M claims records might consume 30-60 RPU-hours (~$11-22 per run). If your organization already has a provisioned Redshift cluster for other analytics workloads, use it. If this pipeline is the only Redshift consumer, Serverless or even Athena over S3 Parquet files may be more cost-effective for the aggregation step.
